commit_message:
generic push driver

A straightforward extension to the doctor push driver to allow for
1. arbitrary schema set in datasource creation config
2. patching (adding and removing) of rows

This patch enables Vitrage and others to push to an instance of
this generic driver.

Example usage:

1. creating a datasource:

congress datasource create generic_push_driver vitrage --config schema='
{
  "tables":[
    {
      "name":"alarms",
      "columns":[
        "id",
        "name",
        "state",
        "severity"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
'

2. Set/replace an entire table:

PUT '/v1/data-sources/vitrage/tables/alarms' with body:
{
  "rows":[
    {
      "id":"1-1",
      "name":"name1",
      "state":"active",
      "severity":1
    },
    {
      "id":"1-2",
      "name":"name2",
      "state":"active",
      "severity":2
    },
  ]
}

3. Patch (add/remove rows) a table:

PATCH '/v1/data-sources/vitrage/tables/alarms' with body:
[
  {
    "op":"add",
    "value":{
      "id":"1-1",
      "name":"name1",
      "state":"active",
      "severity":1
    }
  },
  {
    "op":"remove",
    "value":{
      "id":"1-1",
      "name":"name1",
      "state":"active",
      "severity":1
    }
  },
  {
    "op":"remove",
    "criteria":{
      "state":"active",
      "severity":2
    }
  }
]

Note: the PATCH body format is based on the JSON-patch standard,
adapted to use for sets.

Change-Id: I78e21b1f437550b8470fe0914cd74fe370d20e43
